# MIIE v1.6 Environment Configuration Template
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values

# =============================================================================
# GitHub API Authentication (Optional but Recommended)
# =============================================================================

# GitHub Personal Access Token for authenticated API access
# Benefits:
#   - Higher rate limit: 5,000 requests/hour (vs 60/hour anonymous)
#   - Access to private repositories
#   - Better reliability for production use
#
# How to create a token:
#   1. Go to: https://github.com/settings/tokens/new
#   2. Select scopes: public_repo (or repo for private access)
#   3. Generate and copy the token
#
# Security:
#   - This .env file is gitignored (never committed)
#   - Token is auto-masked in logs (displayed as ghp_...ABCD)
#   - Falls back to anonymous mode if not provided

GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_personal_access_token_here_1234567890abcdef

# Alternative environment variable names (MIIE checks all three in order):
# GH_TOKEN=ghp_your_token_here
# GITHUB_PAT=ghp_your_token_here

# =============================================================================
# Usage Instructions
# =============================================================================

# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Edit .env and replace the placeholder token with your real token
#
# 3. Install python-dotenv (if not already installed):
#    pip install python-dotenv
#
# 4. Run MIIE (token will be auto-loaded):
#    python -m miie analyze https://github.com/user/repo
#
# 5. Verify token is loaded and masked:
#    python -m miie analyze https://github.com/user/repo --verbose
#    # You should see: [Security] GitHub token loaded: ghp_...cdef

# =============================================================================
# Token Security Best Practices
# =============================================================================

# DO:
#   ✓ Store tokens in .env file (auto-gitignored)
#   ✓ Use minimal scopes (only public_repo if possible)
#   ✓ Rotate tokens every 90 days
#   ✓ Revoke unused tokens
#   ✓ Use separate tokens per project

# DON'T:
#   ✗ Never commit .env to version control (already gitignored)
#   ✗ Never hardcode tokens in source code
#   ✗ Never share tokens in plain text (Slack, email, etc.)
#   ✗ Never use CLI --auth-token in production (visible in process list)

# =============================================================================
# Rate Limits
# =============================================================================

# Anonymous mode (no token):
#   - Rate limit: 60 requests/hour
#   - Access: Public repositories only
#   - Best for: Quick tests

# Authenticated mode (with token):
#   - Rate limit: 5,000 requests/hour
#   - Access: Public + private repositories
#   - Best for: Production use, CI/CD

# Check your current rate limit:
#   curl -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" https://api.github.com/rate_limit

# =============================================================================
# Troubleshooting
# =============================================================================

# Issue: "No GitHub token found in environment"
# Solution: Ensure .env file exists in repository root and contains GITHUB_TOKEN

# Issue: "GitHub API rate limit exhausted"
# Solution: Add token to .env for higher rate limit (5000/hr vs 60/hr)

# Issue: "Bad credentials" or "401 Unauthorized"
# Solution: Check token is valid at https://github.com/settings/tokens

# Issue: Token visible in logs
# Solution: This should NEVER happen (bug). Revoke token immediately and report.

# For detailed troubleshooting, see: SECURITY_TOKEN_SETUP.md

